cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.MM

The paper deals with the problem of multihop relaying in millimeter wave networks, which involves communication and networking aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information and communication. The paper also involves the deployment of relays, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper formulates the problem as a cooperative network formation game, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses fairness among different source-destination pairs, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with millimeter wave networks, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
